<subSubSection id="9ECC98D7C753FF9943ADBF5764DEFBAD" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D669CB5CC753FF9943ADBF5764DEFBAD" blockId="2.[151,1436,871,1077]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC753FF9943ADBF57646DFC19" bold="true" box="[151,267,871,897]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Remarks.</emphasis>
After detailed comparative studies of 
<taxonomicName id="11D6B0DFC753FF99418FBF576142FC19" baseAuthorityName="Gyllenhal" baseAuthorityYear="1810" box="[693,1060,871,898]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atramentaria" subGenus="Dimetrota">
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC753FF99418FBF576798FC19" box="[693,766,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Atheta</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC753FF994034BF5866E6FC19" box="[782,896,872,897]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Dimetrota</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC753FF9940AABF586142FC19" box="[912,1060,872,897]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">atramentaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with its related species, we found that this species is in agreement with the male diagnostic characters including aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName id="11D6B0DFC753FF9947AFBFBB60FAFC3D" box="[1173,1436,907,934]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="genitilior" subGenus="Bessobia">
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC753FF9947AFBFBB61C0FC3D" box="[1173,1190,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">A</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC753FF994784BFBB6045FC3D" box="[1214,1315,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Bessobia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC753FF99460EBFBB60FAFC3D" box="[1332,1436,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">genitilior</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described by 
<bibRefCitation id="B247B6ADC753FF99420BBF8064DBFC51" author="Pace, R." box="[305,445,943,970]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" pagination="911 - 982" refId="ref9426" refString="Pace, R. (1998) Aleocharinae della Cina: Parte IV (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). Revue suisse de Zoologie, 105, 911 - 982. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 80064" type="journal article" year="1998">Pace (1998)</bibRefCitation>
. Therefore, the species may be synonymized under 
<taxonomicName id="11D6B0DFC753FF99472ABF9F619AFC51" baseAuthorityName="Gyllenhal" baseAuthorityYear="1810" box="[1040,1276,943,970]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atramentaria" subGenus="Dimetrota">
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC753FF99472ABF9F6147FC51" box="[1040,1057,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">A</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC753FF994701BF806129FC51" box="[1083,1103,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">D</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC753FF994752BF80619AFC51" box="[1128,1276,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">atramentaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. But it is still premature to propose a synonym until thorough comparative and detailed study of the species including 
<typeStatus id="096D75FEC753FF994618BFE46034FC76" box="[1314,1362,980,1006]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">type</typeStatus>
specimens. This species was recorded by 
<bibRefCitation id="B247B6ADC753FF994110BFC7678FFB89" author="Kim, J. I. &amp; Kwon, Y. J. &amp; Paik, J. C. &amp; Lee, S. M. &amp; Ahn, S. L. &amp; Park, H. C. &amp; Chu, H. Y." box="[554,745,1015,1042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" pagination="117 - 214" refId="ref9110" refString="Kim, J. I., Kwon, Y. J., Paik, J. C., Lee, S. M., Ahn, S. L., Park, H. C. &amp; Chu, H. Y. (1994) Order 23. Coleoptera. In: The Entomological Society of Korea and Korean Society of Applied Entomology (Eds.), Check List of Insects from Korea. Kon-Kuk University Press, Seoul, pp. 117 - 214." type="book chapter" year="1994">
Kim 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC753FF994158BFC867F4FB89" box="[610,658,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">et al</emphasis>
. (1994)
</bibRefCitation>
for the first time in 
<collectingCountry id="AEC18BCCC753FF9940FCBFC8616CFB8A" box="[966,1034,1016,1042]" name="South Korea" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Korea</collectingCountry>
and some specimens were collected from mushroom in forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
